  "body": "From the network specs (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/p2p-interface.md#beacon_block)\r\n>   -[REJECT] The current finalized_checkpoint is an ancestor of block -- i.e. get_ancestor(store, block.parent_root, compute_start_slot_at_epoch(store.finalized_checkpoint.epoch)) == store.finalized_checkpoint.root\r\n\r\nIt doesn't look like we are checking for this in the block validation explicitly (i.e. REJECTing a given gossip block during validation if the above conditions are not met), and we should be doing this to be up-to-spec.",
